00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:26,380
 A word is a thought expressed.

261
00:13:26,380 --> 00:13:30,520
 A word makes known something hidden.

262
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:32,860
 It makes something unheard heard.

263
00:13:32,860 --> 00:13:36,780
 It makes something invisible visible.

264
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:38,080
 Here's what that means.

265
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:41,380
 Why is John referring to Jesus as the word?

266
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:43,520
 Because what he's trying to communicate

267
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:47,540
 is that Jesus is God's greatest communication

268
00:13:47,540 --> 00:13:51,780
 to humanity about himself.

269
00:13:51,780 --> 00:13:54,420
 So if you want to know God,

270
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:58,340
 then the best thing you can do is know Jesus Christ.

271
00:13:58,340 --> 00:14:02,940
 If you want to know more of God, then investigate Jesus.

272
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:05,360
 If you have some working knowledge of the Bible,

